         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Stacey Island ¶ New Guinea 29 Aug. 1878 ¶ Baron Von Mueller ¶ Melbourne ¶ My dear Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.08.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Chalmers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dendrobium johnsoniae</seg> (MEL 604265). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 8/10/78'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Stacey Island</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">New Guinea 29 Aug. 1878</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send by way of Cooktown another parcel of plants, my third. Since collecting them we have had nothing but rains, hence many if not all are destroyed. They are from Amazon Bay, Stacey Island, Port Dudfield, country around Catamaran Bay, Discovery Bay and a few from Mount Bohoboho 3360 feet high near to Milne Bay. We have just crossed the Peninsula &amp; since returning home have had no opportunity of drying. Should you find a new one would you kindly name it after Miss Johnson a young lady in Sydney who has materially assisted us in our late trip?<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dendrobium johnsoniae.</seg> See B82.05.06, p. 95: 'Had it not been my particular desire to accede to a wish of the enterprising discoverer of this magnificent orchid, that it should be named after the "daughter of the Rev. Mr. Johnson of Surrey-Hills, New South Wales, a young lady, who materially had assisted the New Guinea Mission," I should have hesitated to describe this plant for publication, no leaves being transmitted with the flowers.'</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will I have no doubt see Mr Chester's report of our late trip, I am sending my report home. <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A report by Henry Chester, 'Judicial Commissioner', to the Queensland Colonial Secretary, dated 20 July 1878, was printed in the </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Brisbane courier</seg>
                     <seg style=""> 12 August 1878, p. 3; an extract was published in the <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>
                     <seg style=""> (Melbourne), 17 August 1878, p. 5. The report included a description of the country traversed with Chalmers. A further report by Chester, dated 27 August 1878, was published in the </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Brisbane courier</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 23 September 1878, p. 5, and extracts were published in the <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>
                     <seg style=""> (Melbourne), 28 September 1878, p. 9. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The report sent by Chalmers was published in the </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australian town and country journal</seg>
                     <seg style=""> (Sydney), 14 September 1878, pp. 11-12.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We leave for home about the beginning of next year. I am in hopes of making one or two more tours &amp; have one good one before me &amp; if time permits I hope to accomplish<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also J. Chalmers to M, 10 November 1881.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I write hurriedly. With kind regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Chalmers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. Should you name one after Miss Johnson would you send her a description of it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Revd Johnson</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>226 Albion Street</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Surrey Hills</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sydney<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Miss Johnson <seg style="font-style: italic; ">superimposed over address</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
